Our family trip to Seoul, South Korea last spring inspired so much of the new issue of Magnolia Journal. Seoul is the place where my mom is from, and where my parents met more than 50 years ago. Even though this was my first time to visit‚Äîamazingly‚ÄîSeoul felt like home to me too. It‚Äôs beautiful how a place, even one you‚Äôve only heard about but never seen, can reveal things you didn‚Äôt know were inside you. 

That story of discovery is at the heart of our theme this season. In choosing to pursue possibility we can, with hopeful expectation, innovate on what we‚Äôve always known. In taking the leap, we can dare to see old things in new ways.
